<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1397,1694]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Remarks: There are two different descriptions of this species. The first one appeared in James’s paper (1933) with a remark that “Dr. Folsom has described this species from material collected at Vicksburg, 
<collectingRegion box="[1238,1371,1561,1586]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
”. The second, more complete and formal description was done by 
<bibRefCitation author="Folsom, J. W." box="[888,1061,1597,1622]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 144" part="168" refId="ref79424" refString="Folsom, J. W. (1937) Nearctic Collembola or springtails of the family Isotomidae. Bulletin of the U. S. National Museum, 168, 1 - 144." title="Nearctic Collembola or springtails of the family Isotomidae" type="journal article" year="1937">Folsom (1937)</bibRefCitation>
in his monograph on Nearctic 
<taxonomicName box="[151,279,1633,1658]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Isotomidae</taxonomicName>
. For a long time the latter was considered as valid, although the former has priority.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1397,1694]" box="[204,545,1669,1694]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">General distribution: Nearctic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
